{
  "texts": [
    "In fact, Felix Hausdorff introduced the name ''topological space'' in 1914.",
    "As an evidence that decision-making can benefit from topological ideas, the Weierstrass Extreme Value Theorem comes to mind easily.",
    "We shall return to this line of inspection in Sect. 5.",
    "We have argued above that sets are ''extended'' to soft sets via parameterized belongingness.",
    "It is therefore only natural to expect that the insights provided by topology would be extended to produce a recognizable part of soft set theory."
  ]
}